<node CREATED="1356758771627" ID="ID_1356710474" MODIFIED="1356763548395" TEXT="Pinjam antar perpustakaan">
<node CREATED="1356758814810" ID="ID_1876296962" MODIFIED="1356764822789" POSITION="right" TEXT="Terms interchangeably">
<node CREATED="1356758855180" ID="ID_130109805" MODIFIED="1356758874076" TEXT="lending, interlending and interlibrary loan, and the terms document supply and document delivery"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1356758912377" ID="ID_405975506" LINK="ill/international-lending-en.pdf" MODIFIED="1356764162130" POSITION="left" TEXT="IFLA Guideline">
<node CREATED="1356759118393" ID="ID_642720466" MODIFIED="1356759413438">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The shared use of individual library collections is a necessary element of international co-operation by libraries. Just as no library can be self-sufficient in meeting all the information needs of its users, so no country can be self-sufficient. The supply of loans and copies between libraries in different countries is a valuable and necessary part of the Interlibrary loan process
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1383457228144" ID="ID_1812466356" MODIFIED="1383457520551" TEXT="Elemen utama dari kerjasama internasional yang dilakukan oleh perpustakaan adalah penggunaan bersama (shared) koleksi perpustakaan. Karena tidak ada perpustakaan yang mampu memenuhi kebutuhan secara mandiri dalam memnuhi kebutuhan informasi pengguna, sehingga tidak ada negara yang mampu mandiri (self-sufficient). Proses silang layan perpustakaan sangat ditentukan oleh ketersediaan peminjaman dan eksemplar yang beredar diantara perpustakaan antar negara."/>
<node CREATED="1356759013912" ID="ID_1784529263" MODIFIED="1356759050218" TEXT="Ada 8 prinsip utama dalam pinjam antar perpustakaan">
<node CREATED="1383458141509" ID="ID_653230571" MODIFIED="1383458165495" TEXT="1. National responsibility. Each country should accept responsibility for providing access to its own publications to any other country, by loan, photocopy or other appropriate method. This applies certainly to those published from the present date, and as far as possible retrospectively."/>
<node CREATED="1383458169670" ID="ID_285395959" MODIFIED="1383458233576" TEXT="2. National resource sharing system. Each country should aim to develop an efficient national resource sharing system, since national resource sharing systems are the essential infrastructure of international resource sharing. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458258520" ID="ID_1103908566" MODIFIED="1383458272792" TEXT="3. National policy for international resource sharing. Each country should have a national policy for international resource sharing and document delivery of its own publications. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458309286" ID="ID_1748927376" MODIFIED="1383458318763" TEXT="4. Sending the request. Supplying libraries should accept requests submitted in any format wherever possible. Requesting libraries should be aware that not all formats will be accepted by all supplying libraries. Accuracy should be ensured at all points in the request process. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458325549" ID="ID_1859431189" MODIFIED="1383458359277" TEXT="5. Supplying the item. The decision whether to supply a substitute copy or to loan the original rests with the supplying library. Each country should be sympathetic to the requesting library&apos;s ability to access the supplied format. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458379815" ID="ID_1752426719" MODIFIED="1383458420244" TEXT="6. Copyright. Due regard must be given to the copyright laws of the supplying country. While material requested on international ILL may often fall within &apos;fair use&apos; or &apos;fair dealing&apos; provisions, responsibility rests with the supplying library to inform the requesting library of any copyright restrictions which might apply. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458421815" ID="ID_1607137095" MODIFIED="1383458451261" TEXT="7. Responsibility for loaned material. The requesting library assumes responsibility for borrowed materials from the time the material leaves the supplying library until it is safely received back. Fast, secure methods should be used for supplying and returning items. "/>
<node CREATED="1383458451942" ID="ID_500538408" MODIFIED="1383458469815" TEXT="8. Charges and payments The decision whether to charge a fee for transactions rests with the individual library. Where such a charge is made, the library should endeavour to keep the mechanism for charging and payment as simple as possible."/>
</node>
</node>
